        <updateDate>2022-08-15T13:47:46Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p>This bill imposes a 100% excise tax on the purchase of a single-family home by a specified large investor (i.e., any person, other than a tax-exempt charitable organization or a governmental entity, with assets having a fair market value exceeding $20 million). The tax does not apply if the home is used as the principal residence of the investor or the sale to the investor is pursuant to a governmental program for providing housing to low-income individuals.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
